   That means lower revenue per view and creators are feeling it.
   Short video ads tend to be placed in between videos, so they're really easy for users to skip, which is one of the reasons, actually, that we have seen platforms prioritizing longer form video because it gives them more opportunities to place ads.
   Most platforms, with the exception of YouTube and now Snapchat, also don't share ad revenue from short form videos with creators, partially because it is harder to attribute an ad view to a short video than it is a long form video when those ads are placed directly in the content.
