 In 2022, frozen food sales in the U.S. reached over $72 billion. Demand has been rapidly growing. Throughout Covid, we had among the highest sales in all of the food space. Behind this seemingly simple idea, there's a sophisticated supply chain keeping perishables frozen. Each step is very critical.
